<Layout title="Reporting Dashboard Fixes" description="Dashboard stability and performance improvements">
  <h1>Reporting Dashboard Fixes</h1>

  <h2>Issues</h2>
  <p>Multiple stability and performance issues were identified in the reporting dashboard:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Dashboard would occasionally crash when loading large datasets.</li>
    <li>Chart rendering was slow for complex visualizations.</li>
    <li>Export functionality would timeout for reports with extensive data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Resolution</h2>
  <p>Comprehensive improvements to the dashboard system including optimized data loading, enhanced caching, and improved error handling.</p>

  <h2>Impact</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Dramatically improved dashboard stability and reliability.</li>
    <li>Faster loading times for all report types.</li>
    <li>More responsive user interface.</li>
    <li>Successful export of large datasets.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technical Changes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Implemented pagination for large datasets.</li>
    <li>Added client-side caching for frequently accessed reports.</li>
    <li>Optimized database queries for report generation.</li>
    <li>Improved error handling and user feedback.</li>
    <li>Added progress indicators for long-running operations.</li>
  </ul>

